headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored eight of his 26 points over the final 3 1/2 minutes Saturday and Myles Turner made five 3-pointers and finished with 22 points to help the Indiana Pacers hold off the charging Brooklyn Nets 108-103.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pascal Siakam's late scoring flurry helps Pacers fend off hard-charging Nets 108-103

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Trae Young had 25 points with 10 assists for his 41st double-double of the season and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Golden State Warriors 124-115 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trae Young, Georges Niang lead the Hawks past the Warriors 124-115

events.name: Washington Wizards at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 31 points and 11 rebounds, Mikal Bridges scored 27 points and the New York Knicks beat the Washington Wizards 122-103 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns, Knicks beat Wizards 122-103 to snap two-game losing streak

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 32 points and 17 rebounds and the Milwaukee Bucks shook off a sluggish start to beat the Sacramento Kings 114-108 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo has 32 points and 17 rebounds in Bucks' 114-108 win over Kings

events.name: Chicago Bulls at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Coby White scored 36 points, Josh Giddey flirted with a quadruple-double and the Chicago Bulls wrecked LeBron James' return from injury with an impressive 146-115 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James' return from injury spoiled by Bulls' phenomenal effort in 146-115 win over Lakers
